They keep telling themselves they can not find more agonizing way s to lose a football game, but each week they surprise themselves wi th their ingenuity. ''Two weeks ago I cried,'' says Archie Manning, their all-star quarterback, who would have needed a tear-gland transplant long ago had he cried after each of the 93 losses in his 10 seasons.

headline.main: EASTERN AIR AND BRANIFF HOLD TALKS

results.snippet: Eastern Air Lines Inc., the nation's fifth-largest airline, and Braniff International, eighth in size but shrinking under the impact of severe financial setbacks, jointly announced yesterday that they were holding ''preliminary discussions'' on a...
results.lead_paragraph: Eastern Air Lines Inc., the nation's fifth-largest airline, and Braniff International, eighth in size but shrinking under the impact of severe financial setbacks, jointly announced yesterday that they were holding ''preliminary discussions'' on a possible merger. Spokesmen for both carriers, who emphasized that the talks were just beginning, would not speculate on which would be likely to absorb the other. But it was generally agreed by industry analysts that, because Braniff has suffered heavy financial setbacks in the two years since airline deregulation, Eastern would do the absorbing.

headline.main: SHUTTLE IS MOVED TO LAUNCH PAD FOR MARCH FLIGHT

results.snippet: Columbia,'' the space shuttle expected to carry Americans into space for the first time in five years, was transported to its launch site at Cape Canaveral yesterday, ready for the final checkouts and rehearsals expected to culminate in the...
results.lead_paragraph: Columbia,'' the space shuttle expected to carry Americans into space for the first time in five years, was transported to its launch site at Cape Canaveral yesterday, ready for the final checkouts and rehearsals expected to culminate in the spacecraft's launch on March 14 or shortly thereafter. The move to the launch pad was a sign that Federal space officials believe the worst of the space shuttle's problems are behind it. The hybrid rocket-airplane, poised vertically for flight, was carried on the back of a giant crawler-transporter, as though on a moving football field, to the edge of the Atlantic Ocean. It had spent five weeks in the cavernous Vehicle Assembly Building, three and a half miles away, undergoing checkout.
